{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"There's an ancient and universal concept\nthat words have power,"},{"time":5000,"text":"that spells exist,"},{"time":6358,"text":"and that if we could only\npronounce the right words,"},{"time":9079,"text":"then -- whoosh! -- you know,\nan avalanche would come"},{"time":11932,"text":"and wipe out the hobbits, right?"},{"time":13961,"text":"So this is a very attractive idea,"},{"time":15972,"text":"because we're very lazy,\nlike the Sorcerer's Apprentice,"},{"time":18623,"text":"or the world's greatest\ncomputer programmer."},{"time":20718,"text":"This idea has a lot of traction with us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":22652,"text":"We love the idea that words,\nwhen pronounced,"},{"time":24814,"text":"are little more than pure information,"},{"time":26656,"text":"but they evoke physical action\nin the real world"},{"time":28939,"text":"that helps us do work."},{"time":30122,"text":"So, of course, with lots\nof programmable computers"},{"time":32554,"text":"and robots around,"},{"time":33729,"text":"this is an easy thing to picture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35585,"text":"How many of you know\nwhat I'm talking about?"},{"time":37674,"text":"Raise your right hand."},{"time":38849,"text":"How many don't know\nwhat I'm talking about?"},{"time":40876,"text":"Raise your left hand."},{"time":42051,"text":"So that's great. So that was too easy."},{"time":44954,"text":"You guys have very insecure computers, OK?"},{"time":48097,"text":"So now the thing is,\nthis is a different kind of spell."},{"time":51749,"text":"This is a computer program\nmade of zeros and ones."},{"time":54130,"text":"It can be pronounced on a computer,\ndoes something like this."},{"time":57012,"text":"The important thing is we can write it\nin a high-level language."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60046,"text":"A computer magician can write this thing."},{"time":62032,"text":"It can be compiled into zeros and ones\nand pronounced by a computer."},{"time":65270,"text":"And that's what makes computers powerful,"},{"time":67293,"text":"these high-level languages\nthat can be compiled."},{"time":69577,"text":"And so, I'm here to tell you,\nyou don't need a computer"},{"time":72457,"text":"to actually have a spell."},{"time":74375,"text":"In fact, what you can do\nat the molecular level"},{"time":76684,"text":"is that if you encode information --"},{"time":78682,"text":"you encode a spell\nor program as molecules --"},{"time":80896,"text":"then physics can actually directly\ninterpret that information"},{"time":84539,"text":"and run a program."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85714,"text":"It's what happens in proteins."},{"time":87170,"text":"When this amino-acid sequence\ngets pronounced as atoms,"},{"time":89815,"text":"these little letters\nare sticky for each other."},{"time":92059,"text":"It collapses into a three-dimensional\nshape that turns it into a nanomachine"},{"time":95967,"text":"that actually cuts DNA."},{"time":97561,"text":"The interesting thing\nis that if you change the sequence,"},{"time":100338,"text":"you change the three-dimensional folding."},{"time":102370,"text":"You get, now, a DNA stapler, instead."},{"time":104354,"text":"These are the kind of molecular programs\nwe want to be able to write."},{"time":107640,"text":"The problem is, we don't know"},{"time":109050,"text":"the machine language of proteins\nor have a compiler for proteins."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112203,"text":"So I've joined a growing band of people"},{"time":114093,"text":"that try to make\nmolecular spells using DNA."},{"time":116331,"text":"We use DNA because it's cheaper,\nit's easier to handle,"},{"time":118959,"text":"it's something\nwe understand really well --"},{"time":121054,"text":"so well, in fact, that we think\nwe can actually write"},{"time":124161,"text":"programming languages for DNA\nand have molecular compilers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":127598,"text":"So then, we think we can do that."},{"time":129203,"text":"One of my first questions doing this was:"},{"time":132712,"text":"How can you make an arbitrary shape\nor pattern out of DNA?"},{"time":135507,"text":"I decided to use a type of DNA origami,"},{"time":137742,"text":"where you take a long strand of DNA"},{"time":139471,"text":"and fold it into whatever shape\nor pattern you might want."},{"time":142304,"text":"So here's a shape."},{"time":143491,"text":"I actually spent about a year in my home\nin my underwear, coding,"},{"time":146875,"text":"like Linus [Torvalds],\nin that picture before."},{"time":149051,"text":"This program takes a shape\nand spits out 250 DNA sequences."},{"time":152620,"text":"These short DNA sequences\nare what are going to fold the long strand"},{"time":155841,"text":"into this shape that we want to make."},{"time":157634,"text":"So you send an e-mail\nwith these sequences in it"},{"time":159905,"text":"to a company,"},{"time":161081,"text":"and the company pronounces them\non a DNA synthesizer,"},{"time":163784,"text":"a machine about the size of a photocopier."},{"time":166298,"text":"And they take your e-mail,"},{"time":168298,"text":"and every letter in your e-mail,\nthey replace with a 30-atom cluster --"},{"time":171683,"text":"one for each letter, A, T, C and G in DNA."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174113,"text":"They string them up in the right sequence,"},{"time":176148,"text":"and then they send them\nback to you via FedEx."},{"time":178333,"text":"So you get 250 of these\nin the mail in little tubes."},{"time":180798,"text":"I mix them together,\nadd a little bit of salt water,"},{"time":183265,"text":"and then add this long strand\nI was telling you about,"},{"time":185825,"text":"that I've stolen from a virus."},{"time":187309,"text":"And then what happens is,"},{"time":188556,"text":"you heat this whole thing up\nto about boiling."},{"time":190734,"text":"You cool it down to room temperature,"},{"time":192820,"text":"and as you do, those short strands\ndo the following thing:"},{"time":196006,"text":"each one of them binds\nthat long strand in one place,"},{"time":199426,"text":"and then has a second half that binds\nthat long strand in a distant place,"},{"time":202998,"text":"and brings those two parts\nof the long strand"},{"time":205291,"text":"close together so they stick together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207360,"text":"So the net effect\nof all 250 of these strands"},{"time":210071,"text":"is to fold the long strand\ninto the shape you're looking for."},{"time":214422,"text":"It'll approximate that shape."},{"time":215838,"text":"We do this for real, in the test tube."},{"time":217691,"text":"In each little drop of water,\nyou get 50 billion of these guys."},{"time":220683,"text":"With a microscope,\nyou can see them on a surface."},{"time":223022,"text":"The neat thing is if you change\nthe sequence and change the spell,"},{"time":226161,"text":"just change the sequence of the staples,"},{"time":228116,"text":"you can make a molecule\nthat looks like this."},{"time":230942,"text":"And, you know, he likes\nto hang out with his buddies."},{"time":233976,"text":"A lot of them are actually pretty good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":235886,"text":"If you change the spell again,\nyou change the sequence again,"},{"time":238792,"text":"you get really nice,\n130-nanometer triangles."},{"time":241122,"text":"If you do it again,"},{"time":242509,"text":"you can get arbitrary patterns."},{"time":244744,"text":"So on a rectangle, you can paint\npatterns of North and South America,"},{"time":249165,"text":"or the words, \"DNA.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":250370,"text":"So that's DNA origami. That's one way."},{"time":253407,"text":"There are many ways\nof casting molecular spells using DNA."},{"time":257374,"text":"What we really want to do in the end"},{"time":259140,"text":"is learn how to program self-assembly\nso we can build anything, right?"},{"time":263000,"text":"We want to be able to build\ntechnological artifacts"},{"time":265414,"text":"that are maybe good for the world."},{"time":267099,"text":"We want to learn how to build\nbiological artifacts,"},{"time":270054,"text":"like people and whales and trees."},{"time":271799,"text":"And if it's the case that we can reach\nthat level of complexity,"},{"time":274845,"text":"if our ability to program molecules\ngets to be that good,"},{"time":278129,"text":"then that will truly be magic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":280889,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":282064,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}